'Philippe' (, , ; born 15 April 1960) is the reigning King of the Belgians,
having ascended the throne on 21 July 2013. He is the eldest child of King
Albert II, whom he succeeded upon Albert's abdication due to health reasons, and
Queen Paola. He married Countess Mathilde d'Udekem d'Acoz (now Queen Mathilde),
with whom he has four children. King Philippe's elder daughter, Princess
Elisabeth, is next in the line of succession.
